{"id":716,"date":"2022-04-06T16:16:00","date_gmt":"2022-04-06T13:16:00","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/?p=716"},"modified":"2022-03-23T21:51:19","modified_gmt":"2022-03-23T19:51:19","slug":"dont-count-on-traditional-banking-lenders","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/dont-count-on-traditional-banking-lenders\/","title":{"rendered":"Don&#8217;t Count on Traditional Banking to Serve Your Lender Needs"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Traditional banking was once the most popular lending platform. However, the increased risk of the internet has led to the rise of online lenders. Loans offer an additional financial source for many businesses. Startups and well-established businesses may require loans to help them expand their business. Ideally, it would be best for businesses to finance their plans. But the reality is most entrepreneurs do not have excess capital to cater to all business needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, most entrepreneurs seek out loans from external sources such as cooperatives or banks. Financial institutions offer <a href=\"https:\/\/www.cnbc.com\/select\/small-business-loan-types\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">different types of loans<\/a>. Therefore, one should carefully decide on which type of funding to consider.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Most businesses opt to go for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/advisor\/business-loans\/best-small-business-loans\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">business loans<\/a> to help them fund their businesses. However, under the business loan category, several types of loans exist for one to choose from. Traditional banking institutions provide long-term and short-term business loans that can extend up to 25 years.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_45 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-grey ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<div class=\"ez-toc-title-container\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Table of Contents<\/p>\n<span class=\"ez-toc-title-tog